body:
I have a mix of options and shares right now, including leaps. Short term (1-3 months) is going to be volatile AF, especially as pipe investors release their shares (total of 850 million shares, 200m available for trading right now with the rest in lockup until various metrics are met). SoFi appears to be a very solid company, the DD I have done shows strong user growth, low debt, good growth, will be profitable this year with over 1B in revenue. They are also pursuing a bank charter and have acquired a California bank to help with that, should the bank charter get approved the stock could easily jump above $30 by the end of the year. PT's are all over the map, realistically WITH the bank charter this year I see the company sitting in the $30-40 range as long as the market stays healthy overall. If there's good earnings reports and continued growth I could even see it as high as $50 with the charter. 

&amp;#x200B;

This is a long term play though, at \~$20-25 a share you just buy and sit on it, this company really offers a one-stop shop in terms of all financial avenues (loans, credit cards, mortgages, investing, etc). The hopium high has me saying &gt;$100 a share in 2+ years, 5-10 years you could be looking at a PayPal valuation.
